Here's the 30-day JavaScript challenge broken down informally:
Day 1: Counter App - Just a simple button-clicking widget to mess with numbers. Easy peasy!
Day 2: Random Color Generator - Instant page makeover! Hit a button, get a random background color.
Day 3: Digital Clock - Get that real-time ticking clock action going.
Day 4: Random Quote Machine - Click for wisdom! Displays a new quote and who said it.
Day 5: Hex to RGB Converter - Turns those weird #ffffff color codes into something more readable.
Day 6: Vowel Counter - Feed it some text and it counts up all the vowels.
Day 7: Modal/Popup Window - Make a box pop up and disappear when you click the 'X'.
Day 8: Simple Calculator - Build a basic on-screen calculator for adding, subtracting, etc. Getting a little trickier.
Day 9: Tip Calculator - Never guess your tip again! Figures out the tip and the total bill per person.
Day 10: To-Do List (Basic) - The classic list where you can add and delete tasks.
Day 11: Password Generator - Need a strong password? This app makes one for you based on your settings.
Day 12: Quiz App - Multiple-choice fun! Tracks your score and shows you how you did.
Day 13: Expense Tracker - Keep an eye on your money—track income and expenses to see your balance change.
Day 14: Local Storage To-Do - The To-Do list, but upgraded! Your tasks stay even if you refresh the page.
Day 15: Random User Generator - Grab fake user info (name, pic) from the internet and display it. Hello, APIs!
Day 16: Weather App - Enter a city and see what the weather is like right now. Time to use some external APIs.
Day 17: GitHub Profile Finder - Look up a GitHub user and display their cool stats and repos.
Day 18: Movie Search App - Search for movies, see their posters and plots. Popcorn time!
Day 19: Currency Converter - Swap between currencies using real-time exchange rates.
Day 20: Dictionary App - Look up a word, get the definition, and even hear it pronounced. Fancy!
Day 21: Recipe Finder - Find meals by ingredients and get those cooking instructions.
Day 22: Stopwatch / Timer - Build your own stop-and-go timer with pause and reset.
Day 23: Rock, Paper, Scissors - Play a classic against the computer. Good luck!
Day 24: Tic-Tac-Toe - A 2-player grid game where you need to check for wins in every direction. This is a big jump!
Day 25: Memory Card Game - Flip cards and find the matching pairs. Get ready to use setTimeout().
Day 26: Drawing App - Turn your browser into a digital sketchpad using the <canvas> element.
Day 27: Custom Video Player - Take control of an HTML5 video with your own stylish play/pause/volume buttons.
Day 28: Typing Speed Test - Find out how fast you can type (WPM) by comparing your text to a sample.
Day 29: Notes App - A proper app where you can create, edit, and save multiple notes using Local Storage.
Day 30: Developer Dashboard - The ultimate final project! Combine a clock, weather, and tasks into one personalized home screen. You're basically a full-stack dev now!